  "time_ut": 1661832885,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0da2\u0dcf\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0dc3\u0db7\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d9a\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0db4\u0dad \u0db4\u0d9a\u0dca\u0dc2 \u0db1\u0dcf\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dba\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0d89\u0daf\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The draft about the National Assembly is presented to the party leaders",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena presented a preliminary draft to the party leaders yesterday (29th) for the establishment of a National Assembly consisting of the parties representing the Parliament. It was during the party leaders' meeting held at the Parliament complex.",
        "The government's proposal regarding the establishment of sectoral supervision committees in the Parliament was also discussed.",
        "Here, the party leaders expressed different opinions, and the party leaders stated that the purpose of this should be to guide the political decisions of the parties in the Parliament by common agreement.",
        "It was also decided to get the views of the respective parties in writing regarding the proposal drafted by the government on the National Assembly and Sectoral Monitoring Committees. It was also decided to prepare a new and improved draft with those ideas and present it to the party leaders' meeting which will be reconvened on Friday (2022.09.02) under the chairmanship of Prime Minister Dinesh Gunawardena.",
        "The government's proposal regarding the addition of 17 sectoral monitoring committees and 3 more to the existing 12 standing committees was also presented to the party leaders.",
        "Leaders of parties and groups representing the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna, Samagi Jana Balawegaya, Sri Lanka Freedom Party, independent parties, Ceylon Labor Congress, United National Party, EPDP, National Congress etc. attended this meeting.",
        "In this regard, on 12.08.2022, a meeting of party leaders was held at the Parliament complex under the chairmanship of the Prime Minister and all the party leaders representing the Parliament participated in it."
      ],
